'''Sir Anthony John Patrick Kenny''' (born [[16 March]] [[1931]]) is an English Catholic philosopher. 

Anthony Kenny is the nephew of [[Alexander Jones]], general editor of ''[[The Jerusalem Bible]]'' to which [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] contributed. Kenny's autobiography includes a [[Index:Reminiscences of J.R.R.
